Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%grams} into 1cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn the tray halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{150%grams}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%unit} or use a #garlic press{}.

Place a hand flat on top of the @Irish chicken breast{320%grams}(sliced horizontally to make two thin steaks) and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the green beans and fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, lower heat to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to medium-high heat a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When hot, add the chicken and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Cook through, ~{3-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Cook in batches if your pan is too crowded.

Add the @mustard{1%sachet}, @chicken stock{1%sachet} and @water{50%ml} to the chicken.

Cook, stirring, until the sauce is slightly thickened and has coated the chicken well, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Remove from the heat and stir through a knob of @butter{to taste} and the @honey{2%sachets}.

> TIP: To reduce the heat in this recipe you can use less mustard.

Divide chicken, potato wedges and green beans between #plates{}.

Pour any extra glaze from the pan over the chicken.